The paper deals with probabilistic classification and aggregation of probabilities from multiple sources, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian methods and prior knowledge also suggests a potential fit for the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also involves measures of bias, accuracy, and dependence, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
